---
import { GlitchText } from "./GlitchText";
---

<section class="border-b-2 border-dim px-gutter py-hero-padding">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-container-max">
    <p class="reveal text-eyebrow text-accent uppercase">// LAZY CAM &mdash; iOS CAMERA APP</p>
    <h1 class="mt-6 font-display text-display font-bold text-fg">
      <GlitchText client:load>Clean, honest pixels.</GlitchText>
    </h1>
    <p class="reveal reveal-delay mt-6 text-body text-muted">
      The stock iPhone look is harsh and over-processed. This is how you escape it &mdash;
      creative control on a clean base, not a fight against Apple's forced HDR.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
